main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Duluth, Minnesota on November 29, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as nondescript but blue-white and green in color., The observer heard dogs barking before the sighting., The object was stationary and disappeared within less than a minute., The sighting occurred near a hole in the ice of Pike Lake., A civilian observer claimed to be a private pilot and former OSI agent.
witness description: civilian, age thirty-five, associated with Chippewa Outfitters, a sporting goods store
